

=Description=

"The Open Imperative Program (Oi) helps nonprofit and community organizations in the New York area expand their capacity to serve the public by training them to use high-value free, libre, and open source (FLO) tools and techniques.  Whether it’s helping an organization deploy a world-class content management system, training staff in hacker-style collaboration techniques or facilitating connections between technologists, activists and organizations, Open Imperative is a local capacity building program with a global objective: align nonprofit organizations behind the FLO movement and align the FLO movement behind nonprofit organizations.

Due to our limited resources, we’re currently focused on serving three types of organizations: (1) Brooklyn-based nonprofit and community groups, (2) organizations involved in the local food movement and (3) high profile organizations willing to promote FLO tools and techniques.

We're looking for three to five small to mid-sized nonprofit organizations in Brooklyn that are interested in receiving free technology support and training in FLO collaboration techniques."
(http://openimperative.drupalgardens.com/)


